What percentage of the worlds land area is forested snice 2015? According to the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO), in 2015, the world's forests covered 4 billion hectares (ha), or 30 percent of the world's land area. The FAO's definition of forests includes natural forests and forest plantations.
